  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "GitHub is used by a vast number of companies and startups across various industries. Here's an overview of some notable users:\n\n1. Large Tech Companies:\n   - Microsoft (which owns GitHub)\n   - Google\n   - Amazon\n   - Apple\n   - IBM\n   - Meta (formerly Facebook)\n\n2. Open Source Projects:\n   - Linux\n   - Kubernetes\n   - TensorFlow\n   - Node.js\n   - React\n\n3. Software Companies:\n   - Adobe\n   - Salesforce\n   - Oracle\n   - SAP\n   - VMware\n\n4. Startups and Tech Innovators:\n   - Airbnb\n   - Uber\n   - Spotify\n   - Shopify\n   - Stripe\n\n5. Government and Non-Profit Organizations:\n   - NASA\n   - White House (U.S.)\n   - European Union\n   - Red Cross\n\n6. Educational Institutions:\n   - MIT\n   - Stanford University\n   - Harvard University\n   - University of Oxford\n\n7. Automotive Industry:\n   - Tesla\n   - Ford\n   - Toyota\n\n8. Financial Services:\n   - Goldman Sachs\n   - JPMorgan Chase\n   - PayPal\n\n9. Healthcare and Biotech:\n   - Pfizer\n   - Johnson & Johnson\n   - Mayo Clinic\n\n10. Gaming Industry:\n    - Unity\n    - Epic Games\n    - Electronic Arts\n\nThis list is not exhaustive, as GitHub boasts over 90 million users and is used by organizations of all sizes across nearly every sector. Many companies and startups use GitHub for version control, collaboration, and open-source contributions.",
